block content

  +state(name, path, 'The Sunshine State', 'March 3, 1845', 'border')

  .intro
    p Florida has flown many flags. Besides its handful of state flags, it’s seen the flags of Spain, France, Britain, the Confederacy, and the United States.
    p An early version of the flag featured the state seal on a field of white. The red saltire was introduced in the 1890’s and approved in 1900. Florida Governor Francis P. Fleming suggested that without it, the flag too closely resembled one of surrender.
    p Because the saltire was adopted amidst the rise of Jim Crow laws, many historians believe it is a reference to the Confederate battle flag.
    p When the seal was changed and standardized in 1985, the flag also followed suit and this new version was officially adopted May 21, 1985.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Florida state flag features a field of white charged with a red saltire.
      p At the center, the state seal is placed.
      +survey(name, '34th')
    .visual.flag
      +flag(name, path, 'border')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-florida-icon-saltire.svg', alt='x-shape')
          h4 saltire
          p the martyrdom of St. Andrew, crucified on an X-shaped cross
          p #[em Note:] As mentioned earlier, many historians believe it is a reference to the Confederate battle flag.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-florida-icon-seminole-woman.svg', alt='Seminole woman with flowers')
          h4 Seminole woman
          p the Seminole people of Florida
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-florida-icon-palmetto.svg', alt='palmetto tree')
          h4 sabal palmetto
          p state tree, regional flora
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-florida-icon-ship.svg', alt='ship with sails')
          h4 ship
          p coastal travel and commerce

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Coat of Arms
      p The seal of Florida was established in 1868. It was similar to today’s version, but in 1985 some revisions took place.
      p The cocoa tree was changed to the palmetto, the Native American woman’s headress was removed to reflect Seminole history more accurately, and the mountains were removed to better show the flat land of Florida.
    .visual.flag
      +coat-of-arms(name, path)

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p The Florida flag prominently features white and red, with supporting colors within the seal.
      hr
      small Florida statute does not provide Cable or Pantone values for the colors of the flag.
      small The hex values here are approximations.
    .visual
